Lagos Bridal Fashion Week (LBFW) is currently underway at the Federal Palace Hotel, Victoria Island Lagos until the 6th of May, 2018. The three-day event, the first of its kind in Nigeria, was organised by Call Her Fashion Agency as a means of filling in the gap in the multi-billion naira wedding industry in the country. It will cater to the needs of weddings and showcase the latest in bridal fashion. The event featured Master classes by professionals in the wedding industry and also had a bridal boutique for both local and international vendors from other African countries, UK, USA and Dubai, with clothes, shoes and accessories sold between 10 AM and 6 PM. Then came the runway show, which started on the first day by 8:55 PM. Click through the galleries below to see all the runway looks from the first day at the event.